Boil a #pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice. Wash the @brown basmati rice{1%cup} in a #sieve{} under running water for ~{1%minute}. Boil the rice for ~{25%minutes} then drain and put back in the pan. Cover with a #tea towel{} and leave off the heat until the chilli is cooked.

Peel and cut the @red onion{1/2}(peeled) lengthways through the root. Finely slice half the onion.

Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, open the @97% pork sausages{1} and remove the meat. Discard the skins and cook the sausage meat until browned off.

> Tip: Break it up with a fork as you go and keep to the side once cooked.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a separate pan on medium-low heat. Once hot, add the onion with @salt{1/4%tsp} and some @black pepper{}. Stir the onions and place a #lid{} on the pan. After ~{5%minutes}, take the lid off the pan and add the @cumin{1/2%tsp}.

After ~{1%minute}, add the @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and turn the heat to medium.

> Tip: If you have any sugar in the cupboard, add ½ tsp now.

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1/2%can} and add them in. Add the @tomato puree{1} and @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Lastly, add the sausage meat and @chipotle paste{1/2%tsp} - go carefully, it's hot!

Zest the @lime{1/2} and mix a pinch of the zest and a squeeze of the juice into the @sour cream{1/2%cup}.

> Tip: When zesting (i.e. grating) the lime, don't go down to the white part underneath the skin as this tastes bitter.

Serve your chilli with the rice, a good dollop of sour cream and a big squeeze of fresh lime juice.